Carefully review the provided git diff and generate a concise, professional MR/PR description. Use this format:

## Summary

[1-3 sentence overview of what this change does and why]

## Key Changes

- [bulleted list of major updates]

## Why These Changes

[explanation of motivation and impact]

## Review Checklist

[Derive specific, actionable checklist items from the actual diff — things a reviewer should verify or test. Do NOT use generic placeholders like "Item 1". Examples: "Verify X behaviour when Y", "Confirm no regression in Z". Minimum 2 items.]

## Notes

[Only include this section if there is genuinely useful additional context — migration steps, caveats, follow-up work, or notable trade-offs. Omit the section entirely if there is nothing meaningful to add.]

Formatting rules:
- Use professional terminology
- Maintain technical clarity while being concise
- Add blank lines after headings
- Output only the description body — no title line, no preamble
- Never output placeholder text like "N/A", "Item 1", or "[additional context]"

